The issue is SQL injection in the password reset token lookup/update flow when the token is interpolated into SQL instead of passed as a parameter.

**Vulnerable pattern**
```js
const sql = `SELECT user_id, expires_at FROM password_resets WHERE token = '${token}'`;
const row = await db.query(sql);
